- "Most active data access users" refers to users with the highest number of data access events;
- "Main contacts" are the primary contact persons for the projects;
- "Affiliated with" means the user’s affiliation matches the project name.

sql:
SELECT MAX(alert_count) AS highest_alert_count
FROM (
  SELECT COUNT(alert_id) AS alert_count
  FROM alerts
  GROUP BY severity
) AS severity_counts;

external_knowledge:
- "Collaboration hierarchy" refers to the structured levels of projects where each project can have sub-projects, and the lead agency of a project can be a participant in higher-level projects;
- "Cumulative access" refers to the total number of data access events aggregated at each level of the hierarchy;
- "Average high-severity alert rate" is the mean rate of high-severity alerts across all stations at each level of the hierarchy.
